Datos Bea

https://github.com/us-bea/bea.R/blob/master/beaR_instructions.pdf

#install.packages('bea.R')
library(bea.R)
library(tidyverse)

beaKey  <- read_file('fuentes/bea_apikey.txt')
beaSpecs <- list(
  'UserID' = beaKey ,
  'Method' = 'GetData',
  'datasetname' = 'NIPA',
  'TableName' = 'T20305',
  'Frequency' = 'Q',
  'Year' = 'X',
  'ResultFormat' = 'json'
)
beaPayload <- beaGet(beaSpecs)
beaPayload
beaPayload %>% 
  gather(periodo, valor, 8:ncol(.)) %>% 
  separate(periodo, into = c('year','quarter'),sep = 'Q') %>% 
  mutate(year = str_match(year, pattern = '\\d{4}'))

Si queremos por ejemplo los datos de Equipment. Table 1.1.5. Gross Domestic Product

Busco usando filter y me quedo con la columna apiCall que me da el cdigo que necesito

datos_posibles_NIPA %>% 
  filter(LineDescription=='Equipment', TableName=='Table 1.1.5. Gross Domestic Product') %>% 
  pull(apiCall)

me copio esa linea, remplazo la beaKey, agrego Frquencym year y ResultFormat

consumo_capital <- beaGet(list('UserID' = beaKey, 
                             'Method' = 'GetData',
                             'DatasetName' = 'NIPA',
                             'TableName' = 'T70500',
                             'Frequency' = 'A',
                             'Year' = 'X',
                             'ResultFormat' = 'json'))

consumo_capital
consumo_capital <- consumo_capital %>% 
  gather(., key =year, value=value,DataValue_1929:ncol(.)) %>% 
  mutate(year = parse_number(year)) %>% 
  select(LineDescription, metric_name = METRIC_NAME, year, value)

Fixed assets

stock_capital <- beaGet(list('UserID' = beaKey, 
                             'Method' = 'GetData',
                             'DatasetName' = 'NIPA',
                             'TableName' = 'T51000',
                             'Frequency' = 'A',
                             'Year' = 'X',
                             'ResultFormat' = 'json'))

stock_capital
stock_capital <- stock_capital %>% 
  gather(., key =year, value=value,DataValue_1951:ncol(.)) %>% 
  mutate(year = parse_number(year)) %>% 
  select(line_description = LineDescription, metric_name = METRIC_NAME, year, value)
